<p>By the way, you have to try a trick we thought up here. We know the Laviano Grid can be slipped out of the Mason Mold cell, right? Well, you can put it in other cells. It's amazingly adaptable! I understand your feelings on human and animal research, so tell you what; whenever you have the time and the equipment, try to put it in a vegetable cell. It's amazing. - <strong>ruperts_33</strong></p>
