<p><span style="color:#35B30B;"><strong>Programme Lekwongole-Pibor (Sudan), in an Infrastructure-Health capacity. [SUCCESSFUL]</strong></span> <em>Self-sustaining, three hospitals and fourteen clinics handed over to other non-government organizations and local workers after training was completed. Semi-permanent or permanent housing for 1000 refugees, sanitation infrastructures for all the residents of Lekwongole also completed and self-sustaining. Local workers trained in a non-anomalous capacity to maintain area and keep discreet application of the Vesta Donation. Programme model to be reproduced.</em></p>
